KWAZULU-NATAL - The ANC’s provincial elective conference in KwaZulu-Natal has been postponed indefinitely. The election of the provincial executive committee was nullified in court this year. WATCH: Chaos as warring ANC factions clash at regional meeting The region is allegedly divided into factions. One supporting President Cyril Ramaphosa, and the other supporting Minister in the Presidency, Dr Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma. On Monday, a meeting of the party's Moses Mabhida region also descended into chaos. Video footage shows bodyguards drawing guns on party members. The ANC’s Provincial Interim Committee Convener, Mike Mabuyakhulu says the cancellation is due to unforeseen circumstances. eNCA